---
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
import { Code, CardGrid } from "@astrojs/starlight/components";

import { ButtonLink, Card } from "../../src/_index";
---

<StarlightPage frontmatter={{ title: "Colors", description: "Color system" }}>
  <header>
    <p>
      Our colour system is designed to create accessible, cohesive, and
      expressive user interfaces. The palette is based on Material Design 3
      principles with a focus on accessibility and brand consistency.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Colour roles</h2>
    <p>
      Colours in our system have specific roles that help create visual
      hierarchy and ensure consistency across our products. Understanding these
      roles is key to applying our colour system effectively.
    </p>

    <CardGrid>
      <Card>
        <h3>Primary</h3>
        <p>
          The primary colour is displayed most frequently across screens and
          components. It represents our brand identity and is used for key
          elements like FABs, buttons, and active states.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-primary">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Primary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#106B57</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-primary">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Primary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFFFFF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-primary-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Primary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#A2F2D9</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-primary-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Primary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#002018</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3>Secondary</h3>
        <p>
          Secondary colours are used for less prominent components in the UI
          such as filter chips and secondary buttons. They complement the
          primary colour while providing additional visual distinction.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-secondary">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Secondary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#4B635B</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-secondary"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Secondary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFFFFF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-secondary-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Secondary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#CDE9DE</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-secondars-4"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Secondary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#072019</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3>Tertiary</h3>
        <p>
          Tertiary colours provide additional visual interest and can be used to
          accent specialized components. They help balance primary and secondary
          colours and add visual richness.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-tertiary">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Tertiary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#416276</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-tertiary"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Tertiary</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFFFFF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-tertiary-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Tertiary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#C4E7FF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-tertiary-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Tertiary Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#001E2D</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3>Error</h3>
        <p>
          Error colours are used specifically to indicate error states and
          represent destructive actions. They draw attention to critical
          information that requires immediate user attention.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-error">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Error</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#BA1A1A</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-error">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Error</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFFFFF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-error-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Error Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFDAD6</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-error-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Error Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#410002</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>
    </CardGrid>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Surface and background</h2>
    <p>
      Surface and background colours form the foundation of your UI, affecting
      readability, component prominence, and overall aesthetic. These colours
      define the "canvas" upon which other UI elements are placed.
    </p>

    <CardGrid>
      <Card>
        <h3>Background & Surface</h3>
        <p>
          Background appears behind scrollable content while surface colours are
          used for elements that contain content and interactive components.
          Surface variants provide visual distinction between elements.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-background">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Background</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#F5FBF6</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-surface">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Surface</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#F5FBF6</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-surface-variant"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Surface Variant</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#DBE5DF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-surface-container"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Surface Container</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#FFFFFF</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-surface-containes-4"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Surface Container High</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#E3EAE5</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Card>
        <h3>On Surface & Outline</h3>
        <p>
          "On" colours are used for text, icons, and strokes that appear on top
          of surfaces. Outline colours are used to define boundaries and create
          visual separation between elements.
        </p>
        <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-background"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Background</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#171D1B</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-surface">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Surface</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#171D1B</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-on-surface-variant"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">On Surface Variant</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#3F4945</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-outline">
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Outline</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#6F7975</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <div
              class="size-16 rounded-md border border-outline bg-outline-variant"
            >
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Outline Variant</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#BFC9C4</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>
    </CardGrid>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Inverse surfaces</h2>
    <p>
      Inverse surfaces provide high contrast options for specific UI components
      that need to stand out against the existing surface colours. They're
      particularly useful for temporary surfaces like tooltips and snackbars.
    </p>

    <div class="not-content grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div
          class="h-32 rounded-md bg-inverse-surface mb-3 flex items-center justify-center"
        >
          <p class="text-inverse-on-surface">Inverse Surface</p>
        </div>
        <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Inverse Surface</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#2B322F</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div
          class="h-32 rounded-md bg-inverse-on-surface mb-3 flex items-center justify-center"
        >
          <p class="text-inverse-surface">Inverse On Surface</p>
        </div>
        <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Inverse On Surface</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#ECF2EE</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div
          class="h-32 rounded-md bg-inverse-primary mb-3 flex items-center justify-center"
        >
          <p class="text-inverse-surface">Inverse Primary</p>
        </div>
        <p class="font-medium text-on-surface">Inverse Primary</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">#87D6BD</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage guidelines</h2>

    <Card>
      <h3>Colour combinations</h3>
      <p>
        Always pair surface colours with their corresponding "on" colours for
        proper contrast:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-on-surface-variant">
        <li>
          • Use <span class="text-on-primary bg-primary px-2 py-1 rounded"
            >on-primary</span
          > text on <span class="bg-primary px-2 py-1 rounded text-on-primary"
            >primary</span
          > surfaces
        </li>
        <li>
          • Use <span
            class="text-on-primary-container bg-primary-container px-2 py-1 rounded"
            >on-primary-container</span
          > text on <span
            class="bg-primary-container px-2 py-1 rounded text-on-primary-container"
            >primary-container</span
          > surfaces
        </li>
        <li>
          • Use <span class="text-on-secondary bg-secondary px-2 py-1 rounded"
            >on-secondary</span
          > text on <span
            class="bg-secondary px-2 py-1 rounded text-on-secondary"
            >secondary</span
          > surfaces
        </li>
        <li>
          • Use <span
            class="text-on-surface bg-surface px-2 py-1 rounded border border-gray-200"
            >on-surface</span
          > text on <span
            class="bg-surface px-2 py-1 rounded text-on-surface border border-gray-200"
            >surface</span
          > areas
        </li>
      </ul>
    </Card>

    <Card>
      <h3>Common components</h3>
      <p>Recommended colour usage for common UI components:</p>
      <div class="not-content flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <ButtonLink variant="tonal" href="/components/button"
            >Button</ButtonLink
          >
          <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">Primary</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <ButtonLink variant="accent" href="/components/button"
            >Button</ButtonLink
          >
          <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">Accent</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <ButtonLink variant="link" href="/components/button">Link</ButtonLink>
          <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">Secondary actions</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <Card tone="failure">Error Message</Card>
          <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant">Errors and warnings</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Card>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h3>Accessibility</h3>
    <p>
      All colour combinations in our system meet WCAG 2.1 AA standards for
      accessibility. Always ensure sufficient contrast between text and
      background by using the prescribed colour combinations.
    </p>
    <CardGrid>
      <div class="p-4 bg-primary rounded-md">
        <div>
          <p class="text-on-primary font-medium">Good contrast</p>
          <p class="text-on-primary">Primary with on-primary text</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-primary-container rounded-md">
        <p class="text-on-primary-container font-medium">Good contrast</p>
        <p class="text-on-primary-container">
          Primary container with on-primary-container text
        </p>
      </div>
    </CardGrid>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Implementation</h2>
    <p>
      Our colour system is implemented using CSS custom properties. To use these
      colours in your components, reference them as CSS variables or use the
      corresponding Tailwind classes.
    </p>

    <Card>
      <h3>CSS implementation</h3>
      <Code
        lang="css"
        code={`.my-button {
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
  color: var(--color-on-primary);
}

.my-card {
  background-color: var(--color-surface-container);
  color: var(--color-on-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-outline-variant);
}`}
      />
    </Card>
  </section>
</StarlightPage>
